sentence: We finally rendezvoused with our balloon , which had come to rest on a dirt road amid a clutch of Epinalers who watched us disassemble our craft -- another half-an-hour of non-flight activity -- that included the precision routine of yanking the balloon to the ground , punching all the air out of it , rolling it up and cramming it and the basket into the trailer .

reason: 在这两个句子中，'rolling'都是指将气球卷起来的动作，没有体现出不同的含义。原句和变异句中的'rolling'都是作为动词短语的一部分，描述了将气球从地面拉起、放气并卷起来以便于运输的过程。两个句子在描述这一动作时用词和结构虽有差异，但目标词'rolling'的含义没有变化。

sentence: In a landmark 1966 ruling , the United States Supreme Court overturned the conviction of a Cleveland osteopath , Dr. Sam Sheppard , for the murder of his wife , saying in its decision , Sheppard v. Maxwell , that there was a `` carnival atmosphere at trial '' because of the news media .
